# ARCHITECTURE

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

For the API layer, well define a HaikuGenerator protocol to allow easy swapping between different implementations and make testing easier using Dependency Injection.
Well mainly use SwiftUI for the UI because its quick and straightforward to set up.
For the image picker, well use PHPickerViewController instead of UIImagePickerController. Since we only need to select an image (no need for editing or capturing new ones), PHPickerViewController is lighter and easier to configure.
Because PHPickerViewController is a UIKit component, well integrate it into SwiftUI using UIViewControllerRepresentable.
